  <title>Week 4 Assignment</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Calculate the following limits. (12)
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 3} \frac{x^2 - x - 6}{x^2 - 5x - 6}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 3} \frac{x^2 + 6x + 5}{x^2 - 6x + 9}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 3} \frac{x^2 - 4x + 3}{x^2 + 9x - 36}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{\sin^2 x + \sin^3 x}{x^2}
        </me></li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following functions, find a value of <m>a</m>
        that makes the function continuous or demonstrate that no
        value of <m>a</m> is possible. (10) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li><me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
            x^2 + ax + 4 \amp x \leq 1 \\
            x^2 - 6 \amp x \gt 1 
          \end{matrix} \right.
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
            \frac{\sin x}{x}  \amp x \geq 0 \\
            x^2 + a  \amp x \lt 0
          \end{matrix} \right.
        </me></li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider a function <m>\frac{p(x)}{q(x)}</m> where <m>p(x)</m>
        and <m>q(x)</m> are polymomials. How many vertical
        asymptotes can this function have? What information about
        <m>p</m> and <m>q</m> determines the number of asymptotes? (4) 
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
